snippet.textDisplay:
I don't mean to disparage your progress, but if you want to make the same jump it took you a year to make in about a quarter of the time, you should really look into the concept of "progressive overload" and pick out a beginner training program such as Starting Strength. In addition to becoming much stronger you'll put on muscle much quicker than you did over the past year. For all the exercises in the video, I didn't see a single squat or deadlift. Neglecting the biggest muscle groups in your body is a common mistake. Heavy resistance training (and nothing is going to be heavier than your squat and deadlift assuming you get them up to speed) boosts testosterone levels which will help you build muscle all over.
It's great to get started by just doing something, but now that you've made it a habit, you might consider training smarter to achieve specific goals.
